<emphasis id="2FF22831FC033C656E8AFAB3FE95FAB8" box="[140,355,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Bembidium lugubre</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="ADEEFE7EFC033C656F6FFAB3FDDAFAB7" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2608940945" box="[361,556,1293,1320]" collectionCode="MCZ" location="Valley" municipality="Rio Grande" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC033C656F6FFAB3FDDAFAB7" author="LeConte JL" box="[361,556,1293,1320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="2 - 6" refId="ref6443" refString="LeConte JL (1857) Catalogue of the species of Bembidium found in the United States and contiguous northern regions. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 9: 2 - 6." type="journal article" year="1857">LeConte, 1857:6</bibRefCitation>
</materialsCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described as a “variety” of 
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC033C656D5FFAB0FBA2FAB8" authority="Dejean." authorityName="Dejean." box="[857,1108,1293,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC033C656D5FFAB0FC00FAB8" box="[857,1014,1294,1319]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">B. mexicanum</emphasis>
Dejean.
</taxonomicName>
Type locality “ 
<location id="1859A2F8FC033C656F5CFA8EFE57FAD5" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:952F4535FC033C666E8AFB79FDABFED2:1859A2F8FC033C656F5CFA8EFE57FAD5" box="[346,417,1328,1354]" municipality="Rio Grande" name="Valley" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Valley</location>
of the 
<collectingMunicipality id="FD5D6E59FC033C656FF7FA8EFD8DFAD5" box="[497,635,1328,1354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Rio Grande</collectingMunicipality>
”. 
<typeStatus id="C23D4A81FC033C656C89FA8EFD0CFAD5" box="[655,762,1328,1354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Holotype</typeStatus>
female in MCZ (type number 5511); external structure and spermatheca examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D39F423FC033C656E8AFAC9FBBCFA48" blockId="13.[140,1108,1293,1671]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC033C656E8AFAC9FDE0FA0E" authority="Bates, 1882: 148" authorityName="Bates" authorityPageNumber="148" authorityYear="1882" box="[140,534,1399,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sallaei">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC033C656E8AFAC9FEA2FA0E" box="[140,340,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Bembidium sallaei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC033C656F5DFAC9FDE0FA0E" author="Bates HW" box="[347,534,1399,1425]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="41 - 152" refId="ref6009" refString="Bates HW (1882) Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. I. Part 1. In Godman FD, Salvin O (Eds) Biologia Centrali-Americana. Taylor and Francis, London, 41 - 152." type="book chapter" year="1882">Bates, 1882:148</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Type locality not specified, with localities specified in several states of 
<collectingCountry id="6591B4B3FC033C656F96FA24FE12FA2B" box="[400,484,1434,1460]" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">México</collectingCountry>
as well as 
<collectingCountry id="6591B4B3FC033C656C59FA24FD57FA2B" box="[607,673,1434,1460]" name="Belize" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Belize</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="6591B4B3FC033C656CDBFA24FCAAFA2B" box="[733,860,1434,1460]" name="Guatemala" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
. 
<typeStatus id="C23D4A81FC033C656D6EFA24FC21FA2B" box="[872,983,1434,1460]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Lectotype</typeStatus>
male, designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC033C656F31FA03FE22FA48" author="Erwin TL" box="[311,468,1469,1495]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="455 - 496" refId="ref6201" refString="Erwin TL (1982) Small terrestrial ground-beetles of Central America (Carabidae: Bembidiina and Anillina). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 42: 455 - 496." type="journal article" year="1982">Erwin (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, in MNHN; external structure and aedeagus examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D39F423FC033C656E8AFA5EFC6CF982" blockId="13.[140,1108,1293,1671]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC033C656E8AFA5EFDC5FA65" authority="Casey, 1918: 61" authorityName="Casey" authorityPageNumber="61" authorityYear="1918" box="[140,563,1504,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canonicum">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC033C656E8AFA5EFE88FA65" box="[140,382,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Bembidion canonicum</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="ADEEFE7EFC033C656F82FA5EFDC5FA65" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2608940947" box="[388,563,1504,1530]" collectionCode="USNM" location="Arizona" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Arizona" typeStatus="holotype">
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC033C656F82FA5EFDC5FA65" author="Casey TL" box="[388,563,1504,1530]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref6089" refString="Casey TL (1918) A review of the North American Bembidiinae. Memoirs on the Coleoptera 8: 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1918">Casey, 1918:61</bibRefCitation>
</materialsCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Type locality 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC033C656CD6FA5EFCDAFA65" box="[720,812,1504,1530]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Arizona</collectingRegion>
. 
<typeStatus id="C23D4A81FC033C656D33FA5EFC56FA65" box="[821,928,1504,1530]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Holotype</typeStatus>
male in USNM (type number 36920); external structure and aedeagus examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D39F423FC033C656E8AF999FE3CF918" blockId="13.[140,1108,1293,1671]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC033C656E8AF999FDD0F9DE" authority="Casey, 1918: 61" authorityName="Casey" authorityPageNumber="61" authorityYear="1918" box="[140,550,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="retectum">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC033C656E8AF999FE9FF9DF" box="[140,361,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Bembidion retectum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC033C656F75F999FDD0F9DE" author="Casey TL" box="[371,550,1575,1601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref6089" refString="Casey TL (1918) A review of the North American Bembidiinae. Memoirs on the Coleoptera 8: 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1918">Casey, 1918:61</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Type locality St George, 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC033C656D55F999FC66F9DE" box="[851,912,1575,1601]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Utah</collectingRegion>
. 
<typeStatus id="C23D4A81FC033C656D9BF999FBFAF9DE" box="[925,1036,1575,1601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Lectotype</typeStatus>
male, designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC033C656F5BF9F4FE0AF9FB" author="Erwin TL" box="[349,508,1610,1636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="165 - 187" refId="ref6233" refString="Erwin TL (1984) Studies of the tribe Bembidiini (Coleoptera: Carabidae): lectotype designations and species group assignments for Bembidion species described by Thomas L. Casey and others. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 60: 165 - 187." type="journal article" year="1984">Erwin (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, in USNM (type number 36923); external structure and aedeagus examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D39F423FC003C666E8AFF19FDABFED2" blockId="14.[140,1108,167,334]" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">
This species is known from Texas, New 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC003C666C45FF19FD6CFF5E" box="[579,666,167,193]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Mexico</collectingRegion>
, Arizona, Utah, and California south at least to 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC003C666EE7FF74FEC1FF7B" box="[225,311,202,228]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="6591B4B3FC003C666F44FF74FE6FFF7B" box="[322,409,202,228]" name="Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">México</collectingCountry>
. In the 
<collectingCountry id="6591B4B3FC003C666FE8FF74FD72FF7B" box="[494,644,202,228]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">United States</collectingCountry>
specimens of this species tend to be paler than those of 
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC003C666F20FF50FE32FE98" box="[294,452,238,263]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC003C666F20FF50FE32FE98" box="[294,452,238,263]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. mexicanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with some specimens having a pale elytral apex, and with more notable punctures at the base of the pronotum. Male genitalia, female spermathecae, and DNA sequences are distinctive.
</paragraph>
